social_posts.post_text:
It is so easy to get discouraged in the music industry. Even with all the amazing support and wins I’ve been so fortunate with, I still think about quitting music and moving to a remote cabin where I’d spend the rest of my days painting. 🤣

Seriously tho, the pressures can be a lot. If you know me, you know I work around the clock. I’ve sacrificed relationships and a stable life path to pure my dream. As Jack Twist says.. “I wish I knew how to quit you”. 🤠

But music is more than just my career, it’s my purpose and drive in life. It’s at the core of everything I am and love. 

All this to say, recap moments like this where I get to reflect on how far I’ve come and see just how many people care about my art are really mind blowing and affirming. It’s what keeps me going.  I am beyond grateful for all of you. 🥹

I’m truly living my queer fantasy with TWO songs in this week’s @sho_thelword ⚰️.

“Things Are Gonna Get Better” - I wrote this w @johnmarknelson when I was going thru a really difficult time and needed a reminder that I WOULD make it out. I still listen to it when I need a reminder. 🖤

And then “Gimme Gimme Gimme” which I wrote with @seanvanvleet and @piercefulton on a perfect, fun day just jamming and being free and weird together.  I also want to take a moment to acknowledge the kind and creative force @piercefulton was. I feel so lucky to have been able to cross paths with him and his brilliant creative mind in this crazy world. 🖤🙏🏼

#lword #lwordgenerationq  #musicians #queerartist #happy
